The Chronicle Bongani Ndlovu, Showbiz Correspondent A dark cloud has engulfed Zimbabwe as legendary musical icon Oliver Mtukudzi has died! He was 66 years. According to close sources Tuku as he was known died this afternoon at the Avenues Clinic in Harare. <img class="alignnone wp-image-434167 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/01/Oliver-Mtukudzi1-680x510.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="510" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/01/Oliver-Mtukudzi1-680x510.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/01/Oliver-Mtukudzi1-360x270.jpg 360w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/01/Oliver-Mtukudzi1-768x576.jpg 768w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/01/Oliver-Mtukudzi1.jpg 840w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Details are sketchy but Tuku seemed to have been in ICU when he passed on. A source close to the family confirmed Tuku’s death saying the family will issue a statement soon. “It is true that Oliver Mtukudzi has died. He was in a very bad state in ICU. The family will issue a statement to confirm soon,” said a source close Tuku’s to the family. <img class="alignnone wp-image-434168 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/01/Oliver-Mtukudzi68.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/01/Oliver-Mtukudzi68.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/01/Oliver-Mtukudzi68-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Tuku died exactly a year after his friend South African icon Hugh Masekela passed on.